Commentary Text: Sandeep Sharma to Shubman Gill, out Shubman Gill Run Out!! Gill is gone by a long way! It's a direct hit from cover, with Rishi Dhawan hitting the target having just one stump to aim at. Gill is upset as he thinks Sandeep got in his way, and he had to run around him, but Sandeep didn't move at all in his followthrough, was just standing his ground, so he's not at fault. It was a poor call for the single. He knocked this full ball to cover, and then just set off. Brilliant from RIshi Dhawan. Shubman Gill run out (Rishi Dhawan) 9(6) [4s-2]

Commentary Text: Ferguson to Rajapaksa, out Lbw!! Rajapaksa walks off even before the umpire raises the dreaded finger. Full, probably off-speed, and on the stumps from round the wicket, Rajapaksa misses the hoick and is rapped on the pads adjacent to middle and leg. That would have gone onto hit leg. Commentary Text: Shami to Bairstow, out Caught by Sangwan!! Terrific catch! Bairstow's promotion up the order does not work. Shami as he does usually provides the early breakthrough for Gujarat. Hardik is thrilled with that wicket. Not all that short but Bairstow was itching to have a heave to the leg-side, goes for the pull and gets a big top-edge, the ball stays up for an eternity before coming down, Sangwan runs to his left from long leg and dives in front to hang on. He did well to keep his eyes on the ball and take it with both hands. Bairstow c Sangwan b Shami 1(6)
